When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

   For example if I have to work from another computer or if I'm working with other people.

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
If I'm working on some changes but I don't want to make them public yet because they are not ready

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?
A fork is a clone of a repository from a github account to another github account.
A clone is a clone of a repository from a github account to a remote or from a remote to a remote.
A branch is a series of commits in timestamp order.
I would use a fork when I want to work on a repository that comes from onother account on github.
I would use a clone when i want to be able to work on a Github repository from my local machine.
I would use a branch to make experimental changes on a project or to collaborate on a project.


