What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?

    We can keep developing our local branch indepentently from the remote , than we can use fetch to open another branch, starting in that known point of the branch, with all the new changes made on the remote. So now we can compare our local changes with the ones on the remote with git log and git diff.

